<h4>Linux from Scratch</h4>
<p>
    Everyone should do this at least once.  Linux from Scratch isn't even an iso or piece of software that you download.  It's just a document, and that document details exactly how to set up a Linux box down to every last detail.  You'll be installing the kernel yourself, downloading and managing compilers, setting up mount points and manually creating many of the configuration files in /etc.
</p>
<p>
    I would rarely recommend ever using a Linux from Scratch box, unless, for example you are trying to create an embedded version of Linux or are trying to create your own distro.

    http://www.linuxfromscratch.org/
</p>

<h4>Logging in</h4>
<p class="doc">
